<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n35214a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35214a">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35214a"> 214(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Kneadingplace / Majan</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">On the other side of the door <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> is a shallow trough, which is said to mark the original site of the stone on which Abraham stood to build the Ka&apos;ba. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> the place is now called the &ldquo;kneading-place&rdquo; (Ma&apos;jan), where the cement for the Ka&apos;ba was prepared. <small> &ldquo;MECCA&rdquo; <a name="EBMC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBMC"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 953</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
